# Documentation & tests (required)

Any **code change** — new features, behavior changes, bug fixes, refactors that alter contracts, new config paths, notifications, build scripts, or gateway/Codex integration — must include **updated docs** and **tests** in the same work session. Do not leave documentation stale or ship untested logic.

## Tests

1. Run `make test` before finishing.
2. Add or extend tests in `Tests/CodexBarTests/` for behavior you changed or introduced.
3. Prefer extending an existing test file over creating a new harness (see `ARCHITECTURE.md` → Tests).
4. Test pure logic (translation, config stripping, catalog parsing) without requiring a live Codex Desktop process when possible.
5. Skip new tests only when the change is docs-only or a trivial comment/format with zero behavior change.

### Live verification (gateway / menu bar)

For **gateway or menu bar changes**, `make test` is not always enough — also smoke-test the running app:

1. Rebuild and relaunch: `make run` (packaging + relaunch — `make build` alone does **not** refresh the running `.app`).
2. Confirm gateway: `curl -s http://127.0.0.1:8765/health` returns `{"status":"ok",...}`.
3. For menu bar changes: confirm the status icon and menu items behave as expected.

## Documentation — what to update

| Change type | Update |
|-------------|--------|
| New/changed gateway route, service, config path, notification | `ARCHITECTURE.md` (routes, source map, common tasks → files) |
| User-visible capability or install/requirements | `README.md` |
| Build, sign, notarize, release CI, scripts | `BUILDING.md` |
| Gateway / Codex integration surface | `.cursor/skills/codexbar-gateway/SKILL.md`, `codex-gateway-integration.mdc` if needed |
| Release/version/packaging behavior | `.cursor/skills/codexbar-release/SKILL.md` |
| Dev workflow, make targets, testing | `.cursor/skills/codexbar-dev/SKILL.md` |
| Agent entry / repo conventions | `AGENTS.md` |

`ARCHITECTURE.md` is the canonical internal reference — keep it accurate when structure or data flow changes.

## Definition of done

- [ ] Code compiles (`make build` or `swift build`)
- [ ] `make test` passes
- [ ] Gateway/menu bar changes smoke-tested (`make run`, then `curl /health` or manual menu check)
- [ ] Relevant docs updated (at minimum `ARCHITECTURE.md` for non-trivial app changes)
- [ ] User-facing changes reflected in `README.md` when applicable

Only commit when the user explicitly asks.
